Author: crumb#2550
Content:
different UI-s built on BarterDEX protocol share a percentage of revenue that they generate. i don't remember the exact percentage, but let's imagine it will be 10% of BarterDEX revenues. 

so if there are two UI-s Satinder's DEX (first BarterDEX) and HyperDEX. HyperDEX will become more popular and let's say its share of all transactions will be 85% and "Classic BarterDEX" will bring in 15% of revenue. Then HyperDEX will receive 8.5% and Classic BarterDEX 1.5% of BarterDEX total protocol revshares. 

in the future there will be undoubtedly more DEX-es using BarterDEX protocol and so the revshares will be divided amongst them, proportionally how much activity they'll have.

please correnct me @jl777c if i missed anything important

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: yes, this is correct
